
[1]awry

   AWRY', a. or adv.

   1. Turned or twisted towards one side; not in a straight or true
   direction, or position; asquint; with oblique vision; as, "to glance a
   look awry;" the lady's cap is awry.

   2. In a figurative sense, turned aside from the line of truth, or right
   reason; perverse or perversely.
